Twitter Interval Data

Get Sources and Libraries

#source("setupCrawler.R") 
#setupCrawler() 
library(ggplot2)
library(devtools)
library(easyGgplot2)

Get Tweet Data Then put it into data frames

python <- searchTwitter("#python", n=1000)
starWars <- searchTwitter("#StarWars", n = 1000)
nfl <- searchTwitter("#NFL", n = 1000)
politics <- searchTwitter("#politics", n = 1000)
dnd <- searchTwitter("#dnd", n = 1000)
java <- searchTwitter("#java", n = 1000)


python.df <- twListToDF(python)
starWars.df <- twListToDF(starWars)
nfl.df <- twListToDF(nfl)
politics.df <- twListToDF(politics)
dnd.df <- twListToDF(dnd)
java.df <- twListToDF(java)

Create Histograms for Inter-Arrival Times:

Python

summary(python.df$created)
                 Min.               1st Qu.                Median 
"2017-02-24 11:13:10" "2017-02-24 13:14:19" "2017-02-24 15:22:54" 
                 Mean               3rd Qu.                  Max. 
"2017-02-24 15:13:51" "2017-02-24 17:11:40" "2017-02-24 18:55:27" 
hist(python.df$created, breaks = 20, freq = TRUE, include.lowest = TRUE,
     main = "", xlab = "Creation time", col = "bisque")

ggplot(python.df, aes(x = created)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 18, closed = "left", color = "black", aes(fill = ..count.., alpha = 0.2)) +
  scale_fill_gradient("Count", low = "aliceblue", high = "blue")

created.sort <- sort(as.integer(python.df[,'created']))
python.diff <- diff(created.sort)
summary(python.diff)
   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
   0.00    4.00   17.00   27.76   41.00  218.00 
ggplot(data=as.data.frame(python.diff), aes(x=python.diff)) + 
  geom_histogram(bins=32, closed='left', colour='black', aes(fill=..count..,alpha=0.2)) +
  scale_fill_gradient('Count', low='blue', high ='orange')  

ggplot(data=as.data.frame(python.diff), aes(x=python.diff)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..,fill=..count..,alpha=0.2),bins=32, closed='left') +
  geom_density(fill='red',alpha=0.2)

bin.width <- 1 
min <- min(python.diff)
max <- max(python.diff)  
breaks <- seq(min, max+1, by = bin.width) 
cuts <- cut(python.diff, breaks, right=FALSE)
freq <- table(cuts)
cumFreq <- cumsum(freq)
cumProb <- cumFreq/length(python.diff)
x <- c(min(python.diff) : max(python.diff))
y <- as.vector(cumProb)
tag <- c('#python')
legend <- as.factor(rep(tag, times=length(y)))
pdat <- data.frame(x,y,legend) 
min
[1] 0
max
[1] 218

allData <- rbind(swdat, poldat, nfldat, jdat, dndat, pdat)
p1 <- ggplot(data = allData, aes(x=x, y=y))
p2 <- p1  + 
  geom_line(aes(colour=legend)) +
  xlim(-1,300) +
  xlab('Inter-Arrival Time in Seconds') +
  ylab('Cumulative Probability') + 
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=7),
        axis.title=element_text(size=7),
        plot.title= element_text(lineheight=.2),
        legend.text=element_text(size=7),
        legend.position='bottom')
p3 <- p2 + geom_point(aes(colour=legend), size = .05)
ggplot2.multiplot(p3)
